  "time_ut": 1661145232,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0ddd\u0db1\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dc4\u0da2\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc1\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Thonigala inscriptions on public display",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Vavuniya Archeology Officer's Office says that the re-copying of the historical Thonigala inscriptions located in Kudakachchikodiya area of \u200b\u200bVavuniya has been completed after 20 years and the soil covering the inscriptions has been removed and they are open for public exhibition.",
        "In 2002, due to the threat of destroying the Thonigala inscription due to the war, it was covered with sand and soil, and then according to the strong request of the monks and local residents, after a discussion conducted by the archeology department officials, the covered soil and sand were removed and re-copied. Archaeological officials also said that there was no damage.",
        "These Thonigala inscriptions reveal a lot of unique information about Sri Lankan history as well as Sri Lankan economic history.",
        "In addition to the main inscription, two other inscriptions are located on this rock. In addition, 2 circular archeological structures, a pillared site and two ponds can be seen around. Prehistoric stone tools are also scattered in the rock.",
        "This inscription was commissioned by King Sri Meghavarnabhaya (303-331 AD), son of King Mahasen. It contains a lot of important information about monastic rule, religious rituals, usury and currency in a trading center where grain was deposited. It is now a place similar to a bank. It indicates that 50% interest was paid on paddy and 25% interest on other grains. Also, it is stated in the article that during this time, paddy was cultivated in three seasons namely Yala, Maha and Meda. It is also accepted by some scholars that the 'Yahisa Pawata' temple is the current Madukanda Sri Dalada temple.",
        "For the purpose of copying the inscriptions, a group of archaeological research officers from the Department of Epigraphy and Numismatics, under the supervision of Director of Epigraphy and Numismatics Mr. Namal Kodithuvakku, on the advice of Director General of Archaeology, Professor Anura Manatunga, re-transcribed the Thonigala inscriptions. Mr. G. Jayathilaka, Regional Explorer Mrs. Piyum Perera, Archaeological Research Officer Wickramasiri Piyadasa, Development Officer Anuradha Bandara have given full support.",
        "However, while the public exhibition of the historical Thonigala inscriptions takes place under the protection and guidance of the Vavuniya Civil Defense Force, it is also reported that there are some obstacles in providing facilities to the people who come to see the inscriptions.",
        "Also, Vavuniya Archeology Officer's Office added that no funds have been allocated for the Thonigala Inscriptions pilot sale and if the funds are allocated, a formal plan can be implemented to protect the inscriptions by providing facilities to the people."
      ],
